  "text": "The requirement that the helicity-0 mode on a FRW background has a positive-definite kinetic term is referred to as the generalized Higuchi bound. This has been studied for the first time in the bigravity theory in [CITATION_1] and in [27] (see also [42] for an alternative analysis of the scalar sector).",
